Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND THE EXPIRATION DATE OF ALL
16 LICENSES OF THE BOARD OF EXAMINERS IN
17 SPEECH-LANGUAGE PATHOLOGY AND AUDIOLOGY.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 17-100-305(a)-(c), concerning the annual
22 review of licenses issued by the Board of Examiners in Speech-Language
23 Pathology and Audiology, are amended to read as follows:
24 (a) Licenses issued under this chapter expire and become invalid at
25 12:00 midnight, June 30, of each year if not renewed each year.
26 (b) To maintain a license, a person licensed under this chapter shall
27 pay a fee for renewal of license to the Board of Examiners in Speech-Language
28 Pathology and Audiology on or before June 30 the expiration date of each
29 year.
30 (c)(1)(A) If a request for renewal is postmarked on or before July 15
31 fifteen (15) days after the expiration date:
32 (i) The request shall not be considered late; and
33 (ii) The licensee shall not be:
34 (a) Considered as practicing without a
35 license; or
36 (b) Charged a late fee.
